{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place 450 g of the water into mixing bowl and heat <b>9 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add dashi powder and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b> or until dissolved. Transfer into a jug and set aside to cool completely (approx. 1 hour )."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place eggs into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add cooled dashi stock, soy sauce, rice wine and salt and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>, or until combined. Strain custard mixture through a fine mesh sieve into a jug and set aside. Rinse mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Divide mushrooms and prawns equally between 4 ramekins (6-8 cm, ensuring ramekins fit comfortably in Varoma dish). Gently pour custard mixture into ramekins and cover each ramekin with aluminium foil."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place remaining 600 g water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and place ramekins into Varoma dish. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma lid and carefully rotate custards to ensure even cooking. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until custards are set and a toothpick inserted into the centre comes out clean. Carefully remove from Varoma and garnish with spring onions\/shallots and serve warm."}],"usefulItems":"jug, fine mesh sieve, aluminium foil, toothpick, ramekins (6 cm)","id":"r129211","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-0qvWXpszeJk\/XZMuAjm-XNI\/AAAAAAAAaAI\/3J6mg1JGl1c27JHEdj19xLNUPJ6dt3K1QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6yjEUCasaRpmCPnS.png","title":"Chawanmushi (Japanese savoury custard)","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1050 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp dashi powder (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tsp soy sauce"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tbsp rice wine"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"3 fresh shiitake mushrooms, stems removed and cups cut into slices (approx. 5 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"8 peeled raw prawns (approx. 100 g)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 spring onions\/shallots, cut into thin slices"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","427.9 kJ \/ 101.9 kcal","12.8 g","0.8 g","5.2 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Chawanmushi meaning \"tea cup\" or \"steamed in a bowl\", is an egg custard dish popular in Japan. It is usually eaten as a starter or part of a larger meal. And it is one of the few traditional Japanese dishes eaten with a spoon!","Dashi is a Japanese stock or broth made from kombu (dried kelp), Bonito flakes (dried and smoked skipjack tuna shaved into thin flakes), anchovies, sardines or a combination of all of the above. Dashi is a fundamental ingredient in many Japanese dishes and can be found at Asian grocers and some major supermarkets."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 45m","4 portions"]}